commit.message: Add two's complement input and binary bits to preferences, and preserve these settings when leaving programming keypad
Do not use Unicode minus in exponent of hexadecimal floating-point literals using 0x...p... notation (issue #517)
Add developer id to metadata
Update metadata; Only use Unicode exponents for units on result tooltip

Fix action for menu of "âžž" keypad button with calculate-as-you-type activated; Fix click to toggle value at binary position with calculate-as-you-type with delayed add to history actived; Fix decision when to display "Decimal Fraction" in conversion menu; Update default options in rot and cmp dialogs; Do not look for units (for conversion list) in angle function arguments; Fix compatibility with old GTK versions
Updates for changes in libqalculate; Increment version number; Update translations; Update manual
Updates for changes to parsing of "where"-expression in libqalculate
Add retry and cancel options (and change Ok to Ignore) to error dialog after failure to save preferences or definitions
Fixes for binary bits setting; Updates for changes in libqalculate

Add new rounding methods; Uses parentheses for numbers with scientific notation in more cases; Change "? bit" to "? bits" and translate "bits"; Use 1 as first index in binary number; Updates for changes in libqalculate; Update manual
Add output of hexadecimal floating-point literals to floating point conversion window (issue #514)

Always show binary position numbers in result if numbers of bits are higher than 16, and improve appearance; Click on binary number in result to flip bit; Remove "ALL" button (opened number bases dialog) from programming keypad; Add selection of number of bits (affects input and output of binary and hexadecimal numbers, and default number of bits for "cmp" and "rot") to programming keypad; Fix conversion to angle unit for complex angle, cis and polar forms; Suggest conversion to angle unit when expression contains inverse trigonometric function
Fix typo in example
Fix x and y are reversed for paired matrix when using plot dialog (issue #511)
Add support for "decimals" "to"-conversion (display as decimal fraction)

Place non-object (e.g. "Fraction") items first in completion (with emty "to"-expression) and conversion lists and add separator in conversion menu before object (e.g. units) items; Make suggestions for multiple unit categories, in "to"-conversion completion and menu, if no single matching unit (category) is found for expression; Support "to"-conversion to prefix in display of parsed expression; Updates for changes in libqalculate

Update menu of to-button in keypad (use completion list and add symbol to item title); Fix category matching (in completion and conversion view) for volume units in subcategories (U.S., imperial, and cooking units): Add Polish translation to configure.ac; Convert to simple fraction if value only contains integers, when converting to fixed denominator; Add optimal prefix conversion using "to prefix"; Replace deprecated top-level developer_name in AppData XML

commit.message:
Create pl.po

Initial Polish translation.

Add result to history even if both expression and result are identical if expression contains a function generating a random number (issue #501);  Improve handling of conversion to fraction with fixed denominator and add to expression completion list
Support for specifying a fixed denominator for display of fractions (using menu items or to-conversion, e.g. "to 1/8") (issue #499); Menu items for percent and permille fraction formats

Fix case insensitive comparison for strings with more than two or more consecutive Unicode characters; Fix compile warning with Pango >= 1.52; Do not duplicate code for expression history cycling; Prefer capitalized function name (over name with underscore), when completing function name
Apply exact behaviour of PageUp/PageDown keys to keypad up/down button, and fix sefault in some cases with unfinished input when cycling through history both using keyboard and keypad (issue #498)
Change order of up and down symbols for cycle through previous expressions keypad button, in order to match keyboard arrow key actions (issue #496)
Improve decision to (not) update calculate-as-you-type result when last character is an operator
Update calculate-as-you-type result even if last character is an operator, if cursor is not at the end of the expression (issue #492)
